Task 2 Create choropleths


(i)

# read in files
repub = read.csv('republican.csv')
repub = drop_na(repub)
unemployment_df = read.csv('unemployment_3years.csv') 
unemployment_df = drop_na(unemployment_df)
# import libraries and geographical data
library(sf)
library(tmap)
library(tmaptools)
usmap = read_sf('./data/tl_2019_us_county-1/tl_2019_us_county.shp')
## TEXAS
usmap$STATEFP= as.numeric(usmap$STATEFP)
texas_map = subset(usmap, STATEFP == 48)
texas_map$GEOID = as.integer(texas_map$GEOID)
tx = left_join(texas_map, repub, by=c("GEOID"="FIPS"))
tx_plot = tm_shape(tx) +
tm_fill("proportion_won", title="Proportion of Vote Won by Republican", palette = "-RdYlBu") +  tm_facets(by=c('year'), ncol=3) +
  tm_borders(alpha=.3, col="black") +
  tm_layout(main.title = 'Proportion of Vote Won by Republican in Texas', legend.outside = TRUE, panel.label.bg.color = 'white', panel.label.color = 'black')
tx_plot

## CA
calif_map = subset(usmap, STATEFP == 06)
calif_map$GEOID = as.integer(calif_map$GEOID)
ca = left_join(calif_map, repub, by=c("GEOID"="FIPS"))
ca_plot = tm_shape(ca) +
tm_fill("proportion_won", title="Proportion of Vote Won by Republican", palette = "-RdYlBu") + tm_facets(by=c('year'), ncol=3) + 
  tm_borders(alpha=.3, col="black") +
  tm_layout(main.title = 'Proportion of Vote Won by Republican in California', legend.outside = TRUE, panel.label.bg.color = 'white', panel.label.color = 'black')
ca_plot

## PA
penn_map = subset(usmap, STATEFP == 42)
penn_map$GEOID = as.integer(penn_map$GEOID)
pa = left_join(penn_map, repub, by=c("GEOID"="FIPS"))
pa_plot = tm_shape(pa) +
tm_fill("proportion_won", title="Proportion of Vote Won by Republican", palette = "-RdYlBu") +  tm_facets(by=c('year'), ncol=3) +
  tm_borders(alpha=.3, col="black") +
  tm_layout(main.title = 'Proportion of Vote Won by Republican in Pennsylvania', legend.outside = TRUE, panel.label.bg.color = 'white', panel.label.color = 'black')
pa_plot


(ii)

unemployment = pivot_longer(unemployment_df, cols=2:4, names_to = "Year", values_to = "Unemployment_rate")
unemployment$Year = parse_number(unemployment$Year)
## TEXAS
tx_u = left_join(texas_map, unemployment, by=c("GEOID"="FIPStxt"))
tx_uplot = tm_shape(tx_u) +
tm_fill("Unemployment_rate", title="Unemployment Rate (%)", palette = "Blues") +  tm_facets(by=c('Year'), ncol=3) +
  tm_borders(alpha=.3, col="black") +
  tm_layout(main.title = 'Unemployment Rate in Texas', legend.outside = TRUE, panel.label.bg.color = 'white', panel.label.color = 'black')
tx_uplot

## CA
ca_u = left_join(calif_map, unemployment, by=c("GEOID"="FIPStxt"))
ca_uplot = tm_shape(ca_u) +
tm_fill("Unemployment_rate", title="Unemployment Rate (%)", palette = "Blues") +  tm_facets(by=c('Year'), ncol=3) +
  tm_borders(alpha=.3, col="black") +
  tm_layout(main.title = 'Unemployment Rate in California', legend.outside = TRUE, panel.label.bg.color = 'white', panel.label.color = 'black')
ca_uplot

## PA
pa_u = left_join(penn_map, unemployment, by=c("GEOID"="FIPStxt"))
pa_uplot = tm_shape(pa_u) +
tm_fill("Unemployment_rate", title="Unemployment Rate (%)", palette = "Blues") +  tm_facets(by=c('Year'), ncol=3) +
  tm_borders(alpha=.3, col="black") +
  tm_layout(main.title = 'Unemployment Rate in Pennsylvania', legend.outside = TRUE,   panel.label.bg.color = 'white', panel.label.color = 'black')
pa_uplot

Combined graphs

## TX
current.mode = tmap_mode('plot')
tmap_arrange(tx_plot, tx_uplot, nrow = 2)

## CA
tmap_arrange(ca_plot, ca_uplot, nrow = 2)

## PA
tmap_arrange(pa_plot, pa_uplot, nrow = 2)
